race.comment: TOO TOUGH (4) ran a cracking race on debut at Mornington over 1200m, getting back to last from the inside gate and rattling home to just miss by a nose. Getting to 1400m on the wide expanses of Pakenham should suit much better and he's well fancied to go one better. OCTOBER MANIFESTO (5) has had a few tries but is going well, stepping back up to this trip at Seymour when close up in fourth. He maps ideally and should prove hard to beat. STYLISH PRINCE (3) resumes for his second campaign having shown glimpses in three runs last time in. He's a free-running type who should be fit enough for this. AQUA STORM (1) is a 5yo gelding by Territories on debut for the Moody & Coleman yard who should be respected off a jumpout win on his home track. ANGIEMARIE (10) could be an improver for the Stokes yard off a trial win.
